HEADWORD: Angostura bark
<hw>An`gos*tu"ra bark"</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦aum⟧⟦nsm⟧`g⟦ocr⟧s*t⟦oomac⟧"r⟦adot⟧ b⟦aum⟧rk`)</pr>. <ety>[From
<etsep>Angostura</etsep>, in Venezuela.]</ety> <def>A bitter aromatic
bark, obtained from a South American tree of the rue family
(<spn>Galipea cusparia</spn>, <it>or</it> <spn>Galipea
officinalis</spn>). It is used used as a tonic, in medicines, liqueurs
and bitters.</def> <rj><au>U. S. Disp.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

